4
00:00:21.580 --> 00:00:24.083
I'll tell you who I want!

5
00:00:26.335 --> 00:00:29.130
I told you I'll call you later.

6
00:00:30.214 --> 00:00:32.633
Yeah. you'll get what you want.

7
00:00:35.178 --> 00:00:37.138
...lowlife pulls a piece on me.

8
00:00:37.221 --> 00:00:38.306
It never worked!

9
00:00:38.389 --> 00:00:40.558
What's wrong with you?
I tell you not to touch...

10
00:00:45.646 --> 00:00:47.773
You want to move your car? Huh?

11
00:01:02.705 --> 00:01:04.748
Get out of the way!

12
00:01:07.543 --> 00:01:08.837
Oh. my God!

13
00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:10.338
Move. move!

14
00:01:16.177 --> 00:01:18.429
They opened fire.

15
00:01:20.098 --> 00:01:21.640
Move the hell out of the way!

16
00:01:27.563 --> 00:01:28.689
Drop the gun!

17
00:01:29.732 --> 00:01:31.817
Drop the gun and get on the ground...

18
00:01:59.178 --> 00:02:01.097
Out of my way!

19
00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:02.849
Move!

20
00:02:22.911 --> 00:02:25.788
Move. move. move!

21
00:02:25.872 --> 00:02:27.248
You get out of the car!

22
00:02:27.331 --> 00:02:29.417
- Get out of the way. now!
- Get out of the car. now!

23
00:02:31.544 --> 00:02:32.836
Call 911.

24
00:02:37.967 --> 00:02:40.303
- And then he went to...
- You! You!

25
00:02:42.180 --> 00:02:43.973
Stay calm!

26
00:02:44.473 --> 00:02:45.641
Call the cops.

27
00:02:45.724 --> 00:02:47.851
Let me go!
Please put me down.

28
00:02:51.647 --> 00:02:56.527
- Help! Anybody. please help!
- Shut up! Shut up!

29
00:03:46.452 --> 00:03:48.871
Stand back. everybody.
Okay. please. please.

30
00:05:07.626 --> 00:05:12.626
Sync and corrections by explosiveskull
www.addic7ed.com

31
00:05:22.548 --> 00:05:24.800
You ever wake up
in the morning...

32
00:05:24.883 --> 00:05:27.095
from the second you get out of bed.
it's like...

33
00:05:27.178 --> 00:05:28.929
every molecule in your body hurts?

34
00:05:29.012 --> 00:05:31.390
- No. never.
- I'm in agony. dude.

35
00:05:31.474 --> 00:05:32.600
What. did you go back to the gym?

36
00:05:32.683 --> 00:05:36.061
Hell. no. Do I look capable
of making healthy life choices?

37
00:05:36.145 --> 00:05:38.314
I went out. Matthew.
Went out dancing.

38
00:05:38.397 --> 00:05:40.899
- I'm choosing not to believe that.
- And yet. it's true.

39
00:05:40.983 --> 00:05:42.776
- Mind if I ask you a personal question?
- Go ahead.

40
00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:45.154
- Are you insane?
- Yes.

41
00:05:45.238 --> 00:05:48.366
- Tell me it was the barista.
- Hey. Foggy. Looking good!

42
00:05:49.283 --> 00:05:50.576
Her name is Bethany

43
00:05:50.659 --> 00:05:52.203
- and she is very limber.
- Oh!

44
00:05:52.286 --> 00:05:53.329
You're my hero.

45
00:05:54.622 --> 00:05:57.833
- Watch it. asshole.
- So. uh. when's the next date?

46
00:05:57.916 --> 00:06:00.002
- Well. therein lies the true pain.
- No!

47
00:06:00.085 --> 00:06:02.463
Yes. One and done.

48
00:06:02.546 --> 00:06:05.466
End of the night. she hugged me
like a cousin and said. "I'll call you."

49
00:06:05.549 --> 00:06:07.593
Oh. that's brutal.

50
00:06:07.676 --> 00:06:10.513
- You know what my problem is?
- Well. it ain't the moves.

51
00:06:10.596 --> 00:06:12.140
You know I got the moves.

52
00:06:12.223 --> 00:06:14.392
That's the tragedy of you being blind.
you've never seen me dance.

53
00:06:14.475 --> 00:06:16.477
Yeah. but I can cite the legends
I heard in law school.

54
00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:18.229
So come on. what is it?
What's the problem?

55
00:06:18.312 --> 00:06:21.690
No wingman.
You never come out with me anymore.

56
00:06:21.774 --> 00:06:24.360
Could you imagine
Nelson and Murdock on the dance floor?

57
00:06:24.443 --> 00:06:27.988
I can't deny
that does sound epic.

58
00:06:28.071 --> 00:06:29.365
- Then come out with me. Matt.
- All right.

59
00:06:29.448 --> 00:06:31.367
Come on. just one time. me and you.

60
00:06:32.993 --> 00:06:34.328
What is it?

61
00:06:35.329 --> 00:06:36.455
You're bleeding.

62
00:06:37.206 --> 00:06:40.168
- Huh. Where?
- Base of the skull.

63
00:06:42.170 --> 00:06:44.087
Did you get it?

64
00:06:44.922 --> 00:06:47.466
No one's gonna notice.
if that's what you mean.

65
00:06:47.550 --> 00:06:48.634
Thank you.

66
00:06:49.510 --> 00:06:51.512
- I hate this.
- We don't need to talk about it.

67
00:06:51.595 --> 00:06:53.264
Good thinking.

68
00:06:53.347 --> 00:06:56.392
You know. Karen's been asking questions.
The cuts. the scrapes. the bruises.

69
00:06:56.475 --> 00:06:58.852
- What do you tell her?
- You have a drinking problem.

70
00:06:59.770 --> 00:07:00.938
That's horrible.

71
00:07:01.021 --> 00:07:02.440
Well. it's more plausible than

72
00:07:02.523 --> 00:07:05.067
you put on a devil suit
and beat the shit out of strangers.

73
00:07:05.984 --> 00:07:10.030
You know. this whole thing
isn't just your problem anymore.

74
00:07:10.113 --> 00:07:12.908
And I'm past worrying
about the broken bones.

75
00:07:12.991 --> 00:07:15.161
and finding you beaten into a coma.

76
00:07:16.620 --> 00:07:20.291
- What about us?
- Nelson and Murdock?

77
00:07:20.374 --> 00:07:22.460
You ever stop to think
what happens if you get caught?

78
00:07:22.543 --> 00:07:23.669
At best. you'll be disbarred.

79
00:07:23.752 --> 00:07:26.214
Then you'll continue to do
the good work we started together.

80
00:07:26.297 --> 00:07:27.840
Do you even hear yourself?

81
00:07:28.757 --> 00:07:31.385
You're my partner.
I don't wanna continue alone.

82
00:07:31.469 --> 00:07:32.636
Foggy...

83
00:07:35.055 --> 00:07:38.517
last week. a client came to our office.
Zuly Almeida.

84
00:07:38.601 --> 00:07:40.936
Claimed her life was in danger.
We had no legal recourse to offer.

85
00:07:41.019 --> 00:07:42.646
I remember.

86
00:07:42.730 --> 00:07:45.023
You recommended an excellent shelter
for battered women.

87
00:07:45.107 --> 00:07:47.360
- And she went.
- Yeah. she tried.

88
00:07:48.277 --> 00:07:51.530
That night. her husband found out
she wanted to leave him.

89
00:07:51.614 --> 00:07:52.740
and he followed her to the bus stop

90
00:07:52.823 --> 00:07:55.368
with a gut full of beer
and a butcher knife in his hand.

91
00:07:56.369 --> 00:07:58.454
- You never told me that.
- Well. I'm telling you now.

92
00:07:59.413 --> 00:08:01.290
Mr. Almeida walked out of his apartment

93
00:08:01.374 --> 00:08:05.836
with the intention to hack Mrs. Almeida
into many bloody pieces...

94
00:08:05.919 --> 00:08:07.921
starting by taking off her head.

95
00:08:09.465 --> 00:08:10.758
Guess what?

96
00:08:10.841 --> 00:08:12.009
Never happened.

97
00:08:13.427 --> 00:08:16.222
Instead. he woke up in a hospital
with two broken arms

98
00:08:16.305 --> 00:08:19.267
and a restraining order
safety-pinned to his chest.

99
00:08:19.350 --> 00:08:21.602
Jesus. Matt.

100
00:08:21.685 --> 00:08:24.062
If I take a night off.
people get hurt.

101
00:08:24.146 --> 00:08:26.399
I don't wanna lose you.

102
00:08:26.482 --> 00:08:29.235
- You won't.
- Promise me.

103
00:08:29.318 --> 00:08:32.821
You want me to cross my heart?

104
00:08:33.989 --> 00:08:35.533
Do not make fun of me.

105
00:08:36.825 --> 00:08:38.076
I swear.

106
00:08:39.745 --> 00:08:41.955
Come on. Let's get to work.

107
00:08:42.039 --> 00:08:43.957
Yeah. I gotta get out of this heat.

108
00:08:52.341 --> 00:08:53.717
Idiots.

109
00:08:55.678 --> 00:08:58.389
Good morning. guys.
You take the scenic route this morning?

110
00:08:58.472 --> 00:09:00.724
- Morning to you. too.
- Morning. Karen.

111
00:09:00.808 --> 00:09:02.268
- What have we got?
- All right.

112
00:09:02.351 --> 00:09:06.439
Well. uh. Mr. Marino's dog
was viciously beaten

113
00:09:06.522 --> 00:09:09.442
by his neighbor
after the dog. um...

114
00:09:09.525 --> 00:09:12.653
defiled the neighbor's statue
of Saint Francis.

115
00:09:12.736 --> 00:09:14.071
- "Defiled"?
- Um...

116
00:09:14.154 --> 00:09:16.365
humped repeatedly until completion.

117
00:09:16.449 --> 00:09:20.494
- That's a dog I want to defend.
- Oh. he's... he's all yours. cowboy.

118
00:09:20.578 --> 00:09:23.831
And. uh. Mr. Maxwell here
was attacked in a bar fight last night.

119
00:09:23.914 --> 00:09:24.957
He started it.

120
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:28.251
Oh. I... I called Metro-General
and the other guy will recover.

121
00:09:28.336 --> 00:09:29.462
but if you are looking at trial.

122
00:09:29.545 --> 00:09:32.298
you probably wanna wait
until his jaw is unwired.

123
00:09:32.381 --> 00:09:34.174
Your girl's a badass.

124
00:09:34.257 --> 00:09:37.511
You've no idea.

125
00:09:38.596 --> 00:09:41.098
Um. and. uh.
Miss Jacinto's working papers

126
00:09:41.181 --> 00:09:43.351
have been denied
for the third time.

127
00:09:43.434 --> 00:09:45.811
Her father's gone
and she says that factory work is

128
00:09:45.894 --> 00:09:47.396
the only way she can support her family.

129
00:09:47.480 --> 00:09:49.231
- Well. tell her not to worry.
- Yeah.

130
00:09:49.315 --> 00:09:51.024
I've already pulled her applications
from the DOE.

131
00:09:51.108 --> 00:09:53.319
Good. because we're gonna find her
something better.

132
00:09:53.402 --> 00:09:55.446
And that's just the appointments
for the first hour.

133
00:09:55.529 --> 00:09:57.448
You wanna talk about our 10:00 a.m.'s?

134
00:09:59.408 --> 00:10:00.534
Uh. what's that?

135
00:10:00.618 --> 00:10:03.036
Oh. uh. the bananas are from Mr. Tate.

136
00:10:03.120 --> 00:10:05.748
Payment for that fender bender thing.
And for you...

137
00:10:05.831 --> 00:10:07.833
Strawberry rhubarb.

138
00:10:07.916 --> 00:10:09.543
You will be mine.

139
00:10:10.794 --> 00:10:12.087
Uh. so. um...

140
00:10:13.213 --> 00:10:16.467
I installed this free trial
of accounting software on my computer.

141
00:10:16.550 --> 00:10:19.428
And the good news is that
I can re-up it every 30 days

142
00:10:19.512 --> 00:10:22.264
with a fake email address. But. um...

143
00:10:23.849 --> 00:10:27.310
the bad news is that...
we're broke.

144
00:10:28.604 --> 00:10:32.232
As in. literally no money.
And our income can't cover our bills.

145
00:10:33.567 --> 00:10:34.943
We'll manage.

146
00:10:35.944 --> 00:10:38.489
I don't know how.
but I know we will.

147
00:10:41.033 --> 00:10:42.535
All right.

148
00:10:42.618 --> 00:10:44.870
Well. in the meantime.
I guess we have. um...

149
00:10:45.996 --> 00:10:48.832
lots of pastries and...
and fruit.

150
00:10:48.916 --> 00:10:50.333
Yeah. and fans.

151
00:10:50.418 --> 00:10:52.044
- Portable. electric fans.
- Yes.

152
00:10:52.711 --> 00:10:55.714
And. uh...
and each other.

153
00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:59.134
Miss Jacinto.
will you come in. please?

154
00:11:01.178 --> 00:11:04.347
Let's see if we can find you a better way
to live in Hell's Kitchen.

155
00:11:04.432 --> 00:11:05.849
Please. sit down.

156
00:11:48.517 --> 00:11:51.687
Apologies. Mr. Nesbitt.
Blood's still up.

157
00:11:52.312 --> 00:11:54.648
Best you mind him. Thomas.

158
00:11:55.983 --> 00:11:57.109
You miserable mutt!

159
00:11:57.192 --> 00:11:59.444
Where was all that fight 10 minutes ago?

160
00:12:17.045 --> 00:12:19.047
Place smells like dog shit!

161
00:12:19.131 --> 00:12:20.841
There's a pot calling the kettle.

162
00:12:25.095 --> 00:12:26.930
Someone get this poor man a drink.

163
00:12:29.182 --> 00:12:33.478
Grotto. you mangy shite.
How's the view up Nesbitt's ass?

164
00:12:39.693 --> 00:12:42.530
Gentlemen. if you'll permit me...

165
00:12:43.614 --> 00:12:45.282
a word before we begin.

166
00:12:47.910 --> 00:12:49.745
This is a night for celebration.

167
00:12:52.998 --> 00:12:55.458
A night to discuss
the future of our family...

168
00:12:57.294 --> 00:12:59.880
the gratitude we feel
for the support of his father.

169
00:13:01.632 --> 00:13:03.884
But perhaps as important...

170
00:13:05.218 --> 00:13:09.472
it is also...
a moment for sober reflection.

171
00:13:09.557 --> 00:13:12.100
Sober. my ass.

172
00:13:18.273 --> 00:13:22.069
Two hundred years ago. our people
were little more than dirt farmers.

173
00:13:22.152 --> 00:13:24.362
struggling just to survive.

174
00:13:24.446 --> 00:13:27.908
They had nothing
but their hopes and their fists.

175
00:13:27.991 --> 00:13:30.744
and they brought both of them along
when they came to America.

176
00:13:30.828 --> 00:13:32.454
many to this very city.

177
00:13:32.537 --> 00:13:34.122
Think you've had enough. George.

178
00:13:38.711 --> 00:13:40.253
Now some of you are young...

179
00:13:40.796 --> 00:13:43.215
so there's no reason you'd remember.

180
00:13:43.298 --> 00:13:49.680
but there was a time
when the Irish owned Hell's Kitchen.

181
00:13:50.848 --> 00:13:54.142
Wasn't a mother's son could
make a move without giving us our due.

182
00:13:54.226 --> 00:13:59.272
and any sorry shite dull enough
to cross us paid a heavy price.

183
00:13:59.356 --> 00:14:02.610
We had the cops. judges. councilmen.

184
00:14:02.693 --> 00:14:05.904
We had the whole bloody city
at our beck and call.

185
00:14:08.406 --> 00:14:10.117
But we got complacent.

186
00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:13.161
Lost our edge.

187
00:14:13.245 --> 00:14:15.956
Just enough for a piece of garbage
like Wilson Fisk

188
00:14:16.039 --> 00:14:18.416
to steal what was rightfully ours.

189
00:14:34.266 --> 00:14:36.184
That's right.

190
00:14:36.268 --> 00:14:37.645
Some of us feared Fisk.

191
00:14:39.104 --> 00:14:40.689
Some. in fact. ran.

192
00:14:41.398 --> 00:14:42.650
A few...

193
00:14:43.609 --> 00:14:45.944
maybe even deigned to work for him.

194
00:14:46.028 --> 00:14:49.031
Siding against their own kind.

195
00:14:55.078 --> 00:14:57.455
But now the Devil's taken him down.

196
00:14:57.539 --> 00:15:01.251
and that. gentlemen. has provided us
with a singular opportunity.

197
00:15:01.334 --> 00:15:02.836
The Russians are dead.

198
00:15:03.754 --> 00:15:05.964
The Chinese. they turned tail and ran.

199
00:15:06.048 --> 00:15:09.342
leaving the drug trade
ripe for the taking.

200
00:15:09.426 --> 00:15:11.178
The yakuza have gone silent.

201
00:15:11.261 --> 00:15:13.806
- Piss on 'em!
- Piss on 'em all!

202
00:15:13.889 --> 00:15:16.599
- Piss on 'em all.
- 'Cause this is our time!

203
00:15:17.851 --> 00:15:19.645
Anyone crosses us.

204
00:15:19.728 --> 00:15:21.772
we'll paint the streets red
with their blood.

205
00:15:21.855 --> 00:15:24.274
And when they're gone.
we'll make your father proud.

206
00:15:24.357 --> 00:15:28.779
and purge ourselves of the filthy traitors
who betrayed their own kind

207
00:15:28.862 --> 00:15:31.824
and make Hell's Kitchen ours again!

208
00:17:35.572 --> 00:17:38.533
See. I don't know. that definitely
sounded like cheating to me. Miss Page.

209
00:17:38.616 --> 00:17:40.660
Foggy. you sure
we're not being hustled here?

210
00:17:40.743 --> 00:17:42.955
As sure as Josie's AC is busted.

211
00:17:43.038 --> 00:17:44.539
What AC?

212
00:17:44.622 --> 00:17:46.083
At least she brought water.

213
00:17:46.166 --> 00:17:47.542
- Oh!
- No. you don't wanna do that.

214
00:17:47.625 --> 00:17:50.212
- You can't drink the water here.
- Josie's pipes have issues.

215
00:17:50.295 --> 00:17:51.922
Rust. mold.

216
00:17:52.005 --> 00:17:54.674
I think I can actually see the bacteria

217
00:17:54.757 --> 00:17:55.926
- floating in there.
- Oh. ew. ew.

218
00:17:57.385 --> 00:17:59.429
See. that... that's why we. uh.
keep our cocktails neat.

219
00:17:59.512 --> 00:18:01.181
Pretend you're abroad.

220
00:18:01.264 --> 00:18:03.308
on vacation someplace exotic.
but no mojitos.

221
00:18:03.391 --> 00:18:04.434
Josie just throws mint in the beer.

222
00:18:04.517 --> 00:18:05.811
- Right.
- Take over. buddy.

223
00:18:05.894 --> 00:18:06.895
I gotta hit the head.

224
00:18:06.979 --> 00:18:09.397
And don't let her out of
your four working senses.

225
00:18:09.481 --> 00:18:11.441
- She's as quick as she is beautiful.
- Right.

226
00:18:11.524 --> 00:18:12.818
She reminds me of myself.

227
00:18:17.364 --> 00:18:20.783
Ah. this place brings out something...
special in Foggy

228
00:18:20.868 --> 00:18:23.245
Are you sure
it's not the alcohol?

229
00:18:23.328 --> 00:18:25.998
No. it's the company.

230
00:18:26.081 --> 00:18:27.624
He likes it when it's the three of us.

231
00:18:29.292 --> 00:18:32.880
If it were up to him. we'd be doing this
the rest of our lives.

232
00:18:36.884 --> 00:18:39.761
God damn it.

233
00:18:39.845 --> 00:18:42.222
- What happened?
- There goes my shutout.

234
00:18:42.305 --> 00:18:44.766
Um. you're going for a shutout
against a blind man?

235
00:18:46.309 --> 00:18:47.644
How do you sleep at night. Miss Page?

236
00:18:47.727 --> 00:18:50.022
You don't get any sympathy
from me. Murdock.

237
00:18:50.105 --> 00:18:52.440
I'm still not sure
who's hustling who here.

238
00:18:52.524 --> 00:18:54.651
All right.

239
00:18:54.734 --> 00:18:55.777
Here's your cue.

240
00:18:57.029 --> 00:18:59.239
All right.
you're lined up with the cue ball.

241
00:18:59.322 --> 00:19:02.284
Six is at your two.
pocket straightaway.

242
00:19:02.367 --> 00:19:04.077
Six and pocket two.

243
00:19:05.578 --> 00:19:06.704
Mmm-hmm.

244
00:19:06.788 --> 00:19:08.373
Fire away.

245
00:19:12.252 --> 00:19:15.172
- How'd I do?
- Well. you've got potential.

246
00:19:15.255 --> 00:19:17.257
- All right.
- Here. go again.

247
00:19:29.561 --> 00:19:31.479
Six ball.

248
